<TITLE> HSC results out Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 24 (bdnews24.com)The Higher Secondary Certificate and equivalent examinations results will be published on Saturday. A press release from the education boards computer centre under the education ministry said on Thursday that the results of this year's tests taken under Dhaka, Rajshahi, Comilla, Jessore, Chittagong, Sylhet, Barisal, and Dinajpur board and madrasa board and technical education board will be published at 1pm. Results will be simultaneously published on the website, at all the examination centres, educational institutions, education boards and through SMSs on mobile phones. The website address is www.educationboardresults.gov.bd and mobile operators will inform all how to get results through SMS. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid will convene a press conference by 2.00 pm on the same day to inform news media of the results, another press release said. Information officer at the ministry Subodh Chandra Dhali earlier told bdnews24.com that results would be published on July 25. Results will also be emailed to institutions. A total of 618,308 students from the 10 boards sat the tests this year beginning April 16. Results on mobile phones GrameenPhone will SMS the results and subject-based grades to subscribers who will register for the service. In the message option, one has to write REG, put a space, write first three letters of the board, put another space, write the roll number and send it to 2333. One can register for more roll numbers from the same connection. To get instant results, one has to write the first three letters of the board, put a space and write the roll number and send it to 2333. bd
